---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import NowReadout from '../components/NowReadout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

const story = [
  `I grew up in Karnataka, India, and studied computer science at NIT Karnataka.
   Somewhere in those years I picked up the conviction that still drives me: the
   whole stack is knowable, from the transistor to the product — and the
   interesting problems live at its limits.`,
  `By my final year I was doing research: a capsule-network architecture for
   segmenting retinal fluid that cut trainable parameters by half compared to
   U-Net. It was published in Springer's Medical & Biological Engineering &
   Computing, and it taught me that a good constraint — fewer parameters, less
   compute — is a better teacher than a big budget.`,
  `At Samsung R&D I spent a year and a half about as close to hardware as software
   gets. The Night Mode multiframe pipeline I helped architect — C++, Neon SIMD,
   GPU shared memory, quantized models on NPUs — runs on millions of Galaxy
   devices. Down there, latency is measured in fractions of a millisecond and
   paid for in physics; there is no patch Tuesday for a camera. I learned what
   optimization really means when the machine is small and the constraint is
   real.`,
  `Having seen how far software can be squeezed at the small end, I wanted the
   opposite limit: what happens when it has to span the globe. After a Master's
   at USC and a summer at Skyworks making TensorFlow Lite for Microcontrollers
   faster (the fixes are upstream), I joined Apple in Austin. I build the retail
   platform behind every Apple Store on the planet — the systems real customers
   touch when they book an appointment or walk in to buy something. At that
   scale the hard problems change shape: peak traffic, availability, reliability
   — the non-functional limits you only meet when the whole world shows up at
   once. Event-driven systems on Kafka and Temporal, holding a 99.99% uptime
   bar.`,
  `That's the arc this site records: the same engineer chasing the limits of
   software at both ends — silicon, where a millisecond is an eternity, and
   planet scale, where a minute of downtime is one. On my own time I place bets
   on what comes next — agents, local AI. I'm building toward founding
   something; the bets are how I find out what. This site is where I keep the
   record honest.`,
];
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="The story of Darshan D Vishwanath — from sub-millisecond camera pipelines at Samsung to planet-scale retail systems at Apple, and what comes next."
>
  <div class="prose-page">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="meta">The person</p>
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      {story.map((p) => <p>{p}</p>)}
    </div>

    <section class="block">
      <h2 class="meta head">Now</h2>
      <NowReadout />
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <h2 class="meta head">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest way is email: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
        I'm also on
        {site.socials.map((s, i) => (
          <>
            <a href={s.url} rel="me noopener">{s.label}</a>{i < site.socials.length - 1 ? ' and ' : '.'}
          </>
        ))}
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <h2 class="meta head">Colophon</h2>
      <p class="meta colophon-text">
        built by hand with astro · set in inter &amp; jetbrains mono · hosted on
        github pages · no trackers, no analytics, nothing watching you read
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-head {
    padding-block: clamp(3rem, 8vh, 5rem) 2rem;
  }
  .page-head h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
  }
  .block {
    margin-top: 3.2rem;
  }
  .block .head {
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .colophon-text {
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }
</style>
